<paragraph id="3340217A403E5F15FCC8FD344BC53B70" blockId="41.[826,1441,702,786]" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FD344CDC3AB1" box="[826,952,702,723]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species is named after the Costa Rican parataxonomist, Yow Cárdenas, who collected and reared it for the first time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A403E5F15FCC8FCA04B503D2B" blockId="41.[826,1442,810,1353]" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FCA04C993B5D" box="[826,1021,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The adult of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FB5AFCA04A623B5D" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1192,1286,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FB5AFCA04A623B5D" box="[1192,1286,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FCC8FCC24B853B3D" authority="(Hull, 1934)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[826,1249,840,863]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeralda">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FCC24B5F3B3F" box="[826,1083,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Copestylum emeralda</emphasis>
(Hull, 1934)
</taxonomicName>
among species reared from bromeliads. However, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FB25FCED4A503B1F" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1239,1332,871,893]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FB25FCED4A503B1F" box="[1239,1332,871,893]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FC01FC0C4B1E3BF9" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1011,1146,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeralda">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FC01FC0C4B1E3BF9" box="[1011,1146,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. emeralda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the thick eye hairs of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FCC8FC2F4CFC3BD8" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,920,933,954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FC2F4CFC3BD8" box="[826,920,933,954]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FBB2FC2E4A7A3BD8" box="[1088,1310,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FBB2FC2E4BA03BDB" box="[1088,1220,932,953]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Copestylum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FADBFC2F4AE33BD8" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1321,1415,933,954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FADBFC2F4AE33BD8" box="[1321,1415,933,954]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FC0EFC494AFA3BBB" authority="(Williston, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1020,1438,963,985]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viride">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FC0EFC494BAA3BBA" box="[1020,1230,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Copestylum viride</emphasis>
(Williston, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
, which also has thick eye hairs, metallic body colouration, and wings extensively microtrichose. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FADAFB8B4AE13C74" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1320,1413,1025,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FADAFB8B4AE13C74" box="[1320,1413,1025,1046]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FB64FB954B913C56" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1174,1269,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viride">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FB64FB954B913C56" box="[1174,1269,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. viride</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the blueblack colouration of the head and thorax, which in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FCC8FBD74CFE3C13" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[826,922,1116,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viride">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FBD74CFE3C13" box="[826,922,1116,1138]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. viride</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are metallic green. The early stages are also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FC5CFBF14B523CF2" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[942,1078,1147,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeralda">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FC5CFBF14B523CF2" box="[942,1078,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. emeralda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are easily separated by the posterior breathing tube, which is about as wide as deep in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FC61FB334C943CAC" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[915,1008,1209,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FC61FB334C943CAC" box="[915,1008,1209,1230]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and parallel sided, but in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FAE8FB334AC53CAF" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1306,1441,1208,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeralda">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FAE8FB334AC53CAF" box="[1306,1441,1208,1230]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. emeralda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is about twice as wide as deep and tapers above the transverse ridge. Also, the openings on the pupal spiracles are on the apical half, but in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FB29FA9F4A5D3D48" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1243,1337,1301,1322]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yowoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FB29FA9F4A5D3D48" box="[1243,1337,1301,1322]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">C. yowoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are clustered at the apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A403E5F15FCC8FAEB4BA33DF4" blockId="41.[826,1442,1377,1430]" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCC8FAEB4CF13D14" box="[826,917,1377,1398]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">Biology:</emphasis>
Reared from larvae found in decaying flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FCA5FA0A4B683DF7" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[855,1036,1408,1429]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hemispherica">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403E5F15FCA5FA0A4B683DF7" box="[855,1036,1408,1429]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="308">B. hemispherica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403E5F15FBEEFA0A4BDF3DF4" box="[1052,1211,1408,1430]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="41" pageNumber="308" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
